Package: abcR
Type: Package
Title: Tools Supporting the Adjusted Bayesian Completion Rates (ABC) Model
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Bilal", "Barakat", email="bf.barakat@unesco.org", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Ameer", "Dharamshi", email="ameerdharamshi@gmail.com", role = c("aut")))
Description: The Adjusted Bayesian Completion Rates (ABC) Model is a framework for 
    estimating school completion rates as part of the SDG 4 monitoring initiatives. 
    The abcR packages contains functions supporting said estimation at every step,
    ranging from data construction, pre-processing, model execution, post-processing,
    and plotting. More about the model can be read here (INSERT REPORT HERE!)
